title: Gymnastics: Olympic-bound Tan not floored by loss of coach
title_page: Gymnastics: Olympic-bound Tan not floored by loss of coach | The Straits Times
maintext:
SINGAPORE - National gymnast Tan Sze En may have lost her coach a year before the Tokyo Olympics, but the 19-year-old stressed that the departure of former national coach Gerrit Beltman will not significantly affect her preparations for the rescheduled Games.
Calling the Dutchman's resignation a loss for Singapore Gymnastics (SG), she said: "Technique-wise, he was a great coach and he pushed us to be the best that we could be without compromising our health or safety.
